    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-02-04T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-02-04T15:00:00-05:00" n="452"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d452">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/1008: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-04T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 4, 1933—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>25. Department’s telegram No. 16, February 3, 6 p.m. Personal for Rublee. Do I
                    understand your telegram correctly<note n="90" xml:id="d452fn90">In telegram No.
                        17, February 6, noon, the Secretary of State replied for Mr. Rublee: “Your
                        understanding my telegram is correct.”</note> as follows: Peru would turn
                    over Leticia at once to Brazil; conference would start at once Rio de Janeiro
                    and no matter what result conference Brazil would deliver Leticia to Colombia at
                    expiration of 60 days? Olaya would accept that formula but would not propose it
                    to Brazil as Brazilian Minister for Foreign Affairs has declared efforts at
                    mediation ended and he wants to be free to have Vasocobo [<hi rend="italic"
                        >Vasquez Gobo?</hi>] move early next week (public patience with the
                    Government may be exhausted any moment).</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
